methods.name: name

methods.name: isEmpty

methods.name: matches

methods.name: isInLove

methods.desc: Checks if the specified item can be used to breed this animal.

methods.name: name
methods.desc: Gets the registry name of this item.

methods.name: stackSize
methods.desc: Gets the number of items that are in this stack of items.

methods.name: isEmpty
methods.desc: Checks if this item is an empty slot.

methods.name: displayName
methods.desc: Gets the display name of this item.

methods.name: maxStackSize
methods.desc: Gets the number of items that can be stacked in a single slot for this item type.

methods.name: nbt
methods.desc: Gets the NBT compound tag of this item.

methods.name: damage
methods.desc: Gets the damage (durability removed) of this item. Alternatively, its metadata if it has any.

methods.name: isEnchanted
methods.desc: Checks if this item has any enchantments.

methods.name: getEnchantmentLevel
methods.desc: Gets the level of the specified enchantment on this item, or 0 if the enchantment is not present.

methods.name: isWeapon
methods.desc: Checks if this item has an added Attack Damage value greater than 0.

methods.name: suitType
methods.desc: Gets the suit type of this item, if it is a piece of superhero armor.

methods.name: hasEnchantment
methods.desc: Checks if this item has the specified enchantment.

methods.name: isRenamed
methods.desc: Checks if this item has been renamed in an anvil.

methods.name: maxDamage
methods.desc: Gets the max durability of this item, i.e. how much damage it can take before breaking.

methods.name: biome
methods.desc: Gets the name of the biome in this location.

methods.name: canRain
methods.desc: Checks if it can rain in the biome in this location.

methods.name: canSnow
methods.desc: Checks if it can snow in the biome in this location.

methods.name: getStructure
methods.desc: Gets the id of the structure which exists in this location, if any. If none exists, "null" is returned.

methods.name: getTemperature
methods.desc: Gets the temperature of the biome in this location, as represented by a (seemingly) arbitrary number. Higher number means higher temperature, but it doesn't correspond to any specific unit of measurement.

methods.name: isHighHumidity
methods.desc: Checks if the rainfall of the biome in this location is extremely high.

methods.name: getRainfall
methods.desc: Gets the rainfall of the biome in this location, as represented by a (seemingly) arbitrary number. Higher number means higher rainfall, but it doesn't correspond to any specific unit of measurement.

methods.name: getSlimeSize
methods.desc: Gets the size of this slime. 1=smallest size

methods.name: getBoolean

methods.name: getByte

methods.name: getShort

methods.name: getFloat
methods.desc: Gets the (Float) value of the sub-tag with the specified key, or 0 if no such key is stored.

methods.name: getDouble

methods.name: getFloatList

methods.name: getDoubleList
methods.desc: Gets the (JSNBTList) value of the sub-tag with the specified key, or a new empty NBT list if no such key is stored. Validates that the tag type stored within is Double.

methods.name: isWitherSkeleton

methods.name: name
methods.desc: Gets the name of the damage type.

methods.name: isAbsolute
methods.desc: Checks if this damage cannot be modified by potion effects or enchantments.

methods.name: isMagicDamage
methods.desc: Checks if this damage was magic-related (i.e. it has the "MAGIC" damage type)

methods.name: isExplosion
methods.desc: Checks if this damage was explosive (i.e. it has the "EXPLOSION" damage type)

methods.name: isFireDamage
methods.desc: Checks if this damage was fire-related (i.e. it has the "FIRE" damage type)

methods.name: isIndirect
methods.desc: Checks if this damage was dealt by an attacker indirectly, e.g. from a beam.

methods.name: isMelee
methods.desc: Checks if this damage can be considered melee damage.

methods.name: isProjectile
methods.desc: Checks if this damage was dealt by a projectile.

methods.name: isUnblockable
methods.desc: Checks if this damage cannot be blocked by armor.

methods.desc: Gets the entity who responsible for dealing this damage, if any.

methods.name: canHarmInCreative
methods.desc: Checks if this damage can hurt players who are in creative mode, like void damage does.

methods.name: isDifficultyScaled
methods.desc: Checks if this damage cannot be modified by potion effects or enchantments.

methods.name: name
methods.desc: Gets the registry name of this modifier.

methods.name: getProperty
methods.desc: Gets for this modifier the value associated with the specified modifier property.

methods.desc: Gets the associated id assigned to this modifier using bar notation (domain:name|id), or the registry name if it does not have one.

methods.name: power
methods.desc: Gets the power to which this modifier belongs.

methods.name: isCreativeMode
methods.desc: Checks if this player is in creative mode.

methods.desc: Checks if this player is currently using an item (e.g., bow, food, sword) by holding down the useItemButton (right-click).

methods.name: isBlocking
methods.desc: Checks if this player is currently using an item (e.g., sword) to block by holding down the useItemButton (right-click).

methods.desc: Gets the current experience level that this player is at.
